{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# S6 — Apply the GitHub mirror lock (repo-level ruleset, deploy-key-only push)\n\n## Why\nEnforce that GitHub `main` can ONLY be advanced by the Gerrit replication deploy key. The lock\nis a REPO-LEVEL ruleset (navapbc is a free org -> admin-proof ORG-level rulesets need a paid\nplan; trusted-admin editability is the accepted risk, recorded in S6-pre's ADR). This story\napplies the lock that S6-pre prepared (snapshot + ADR + backend/token).\n\n## What\n- REPLACE the existing `main-protection` ruleset (id 18048287, snapshotted in S6-pre) with the\n  mirror lock — the PR/status-checks model is incompatible with deploy-key-only push.\n- A repo-level ruleset (enforcement `active`) on `main` (+ the branches the bot pushes): rules\n  `update` + `creation` + `deletion` + `non_fast_forward`; bypass list = EXACTLY the\n  replication deploy key in \"Always allow\" mode. A SEPARATE `refs/tags/**` ruleset with the\n  SAME rules + SAME bypass (else tag pushes are rejected).\n- **DeployKey bypass via a committed, idempotent `gh api` step** (the UI omits DeployKey as a\n  bypass actor; terraform-provider-github historically rejects `actor_type=\"DeployKey\"`):\n  `PUT /repos/navapbc/rebar/rulesets/{id}` (full-object replacement -> idempotent), actor\n  `{actor_type:\"DeployKey\", actor_id:<deploy-key-id>, bypass_mode:\"always\"}`. GitHub's docs\n  say `actor_id` is `null` for DeployKey, but that is an UNVERIFIED live behavior with a\n  lockout risk, so the step passes the **numeric deploy-key ID** from\n  `data.github_repository_deploy_key` and falls back to `null` only if the live API rejects the\n  numeric form — and EITHER way the bypass is verified (ordering step 3) before enforcement\n  flips. It is wrapped in a Terraform `null_resource` (`local-exec` + `depends_on`); the\n  `github_repository_ruleset` resources carry **`lifecycle { ignore_changes = [enforcement] }`**\n  so the `null_resource` owns `enforcement` and Terraform never reverts it to `disabled` (no\n  state drift on re-apply).\n- **Self-lockout-safe ordering + bypass VERIFICATION, ONE `terraform apply`:** (1) create both\n  rulesets `enforcement = disabled`; (2) a `null_resource` registers the DeployKey bypass via\n  the `gh api` PUT (`depends_on` the rulesets); (3) **verify the bypass actually resolves** — a\n  `null_resource` reads each ruleset back (`gh api`) and asserts the DeployKey bypass entry is\n  present, and a deploy-key push smoke-test succeeds while a non-bypass push is rejected; (4)\n  only then a final `null_resource` flips both rulesets to `enforcement = active` (`depends_on`\n  step 3). Enforcement is NEVER activated with an empty or unverified bypass — no replication\n  lockout.\n- Consume S5's deploy key via a `data \"github_repository_deploy_key\"` (or a remote-state ref to\n  S5's output) — NOT a hand-copied ID; the apply fails loudly if the key is absent.\n- Mirror hygiene: turn OFF Pull Requests (Feb-2026 repo setting), disable Issues + Actions; add\n  a \"mirror — contribute via Gerrit at rebar.solutions.navateam.com\" banner to the About +\n  README; do NOT archive (archiving freezes the replication bot too).\n- Rollback (runnable in ~15 min): `gh api PATCH .../rulesets/{id} -f enforcement=disabled` to\n  suspend the lock, restore `main-protection` from S6-pre's snapshot, re-enable PRs/Issues/Actions.\n\n## Scope\nIn: ruleset creation/enforcement + DeployKey bypass + ordering + mirror hygiene + rollback.\nOut: the snapshot/ADR/token-scope pre-work (S6-pre); the Gerrit-side replication (S5).\n**Dependency:** apply AFTER S6-pre (snapshot + ADR + backend ready) AND S5 (the deploy key exists).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/terraform/github.tf` — provider pin, remote backend, sensitive token var, the two\n  `github_repository_ruleset` resources (created `disabled`, with `ignore_changes=[enforcement]`),\n  the `data.github_repository_deploy_key` lookup, the repo-feature toggles (PRs/Issues/Actions\n  off, banner), and the two `null_resource`s (bypass PUT, then enforcement flip).\n- `infra/github/set-bypass-actor.sh` — the idempotent `gh api PUT` (full-object `bypass_actors`\n  replacement; the validated DeployKey payload).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A direct `git push` / PR-merge to `main` by a non-bypass identity is REJECTED; force-push\n      and deletion of `main` are REJECTED.\n- [ ] A tag push by a non-bypass identity is REJECTED by the separate `refs/tags/**` ruleset.\n- [ ] The replication deploy key CAN push `main` and tags (the SOLE bypass actor, \"Always\n      allow\", on both rulesets).\n- [ ] The DeployKey bypass is set via the committed `gh api` PUT (`actor_type:\"DeployKey\"`,\n      `bypass_mode:\"always\"`, `actor_id` = the numeric deploy-key id with a `null` fallback), is\n      the ONLY bypass entry, and re-running the apply is idempotent.\n- [ ] **Bypass verified before enforcement.** Before either ruleset is flipped to `active`, the\n      apply reads the ruleset back and confirms the DeployKey bypass entry resolves, and a\n      deploy-key push smoke-test succeeds while a non-bypass push is rejected; enforcement is\n      never activated with an unverified/empty bypass (no replication lockout).\n- [ ] The `github_repository_ruleset` resources carry `lifecycle { ignore_changes = [enforcement] }`;\n      a repeat `terraform apply` shows NO drift on `enforcement` (the `null_resource` owns it).\n- [ ] Ordering holds: rulesets created `disabled` -> bypass registered -> enforcement `active`;\n      `gh api` shows each ruleset `active` WITH the DeployKey bypass present (never `active` +\n      empty bypass).\n- [ ] S6 obtains the deploy key via a data source / remote-state ref (not a hand-copied ID);\n      applying before S5's key exists fails loudly.\n- [ ] PRs disabled, Issues disabled, Actions disabled; README/About carry the mirror banner;\n      repo NOT archived; the existing `main-protection` ruleset is replaced.\n- [ ] A rollback runnable in ~15 min is documented (PATCH `enforcement=disabled`, restore\n      `main-protection` from the S6-pre snapshot, re-enable PRs/Issues/Actions)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782693732848961001,"uuid":"9ea4de58-f23a-4ca1-b3ef-9d50a892b8d7"}